.SH "IMPLEMENTING"
.IX Header "IMPLEMENTING"
This role also performs Email::MIME::Kit::Role::Component.
.PP
This is a role more likely to be consumed than implemented.  It wraps \f(CW\*(C`around\*(C'\fR
the \f(CW\*(C`read_manifest\*(C'\fR method in the consuming class, and \*(L"desugars\*(R" the contents
of the loaded manifest before returning it.
.PP
At present, desugaring is what allows the \f(CW\*(C`type\*(C'\fR attribute in attachments and
alternatives to be given instead of a \f(CW\*(C`content_type\*(C'\fR entry in the
\&\f(CW\*(C`attributes\*(C'\fR entry.  In other words, desugaring turns:
.PP
.Vb 4
\&  {
\&    header => [ ... ],
\&    type   => \*(Aqtext/plain\*(Aq,
\&  }
.Ve
.PP
Into:
.PP
.Vb 4
\&  {
\&    header => [ ... ],
\&    attributes => { content_type => \*(Aqtext/plain\*(Aq },
\&  }
.Ve
.PP
More behavior may be added to the desugarer later.
